comments: At first I saw that all the words ended in cow, so i would try to remember each shape telling out loud the first part of the word. After the 10th-11th shape in which i saw little progress towards learning the language i used paper and gave each shape a number. Circle for example was number 1. so i would say 1 -> 1 is wopy -> wopycow. I used it until 15-16th shape, after which i had already learnt the name of each shape. (the reminder in each round which projected 4 shapes was extremely helpful). The only "problem" i faced was that sometimes i was confusing zetycow with gafycow - propably because the 2 shapes were similar to each other.
